{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "64c0e7736f5bfc7ab78ae4f3", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 60, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": null, "classes": [], "exams": ["615d7713c52ffa3c944600e3"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9e"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "61a8bf0cc821b6514e527d73", "title": "BITSAT 2009", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "A conducting circular loop of radius $r$ carries a constant current $i .$ It is placed in a uniform magnetic field $\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{B}}_{0}$ such that $\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{B}}_{0}$ is perpendicular to the plane of the loop. The magnetic force acting on the loop is", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "qGyG7", "text": "$i r \\mathrm{~B}_{0}$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "qCtG4", "text": "$2 \\pi i r \\mathrm{~B}_{0}$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "Iltfm", "text": "zero", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "PoI0u", "text": "$\\pi$ ir $\\mathrm{B}_{0}$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "The magnetic field is perpendicular to the plane of the paper. Let us consider two diametrically opposite elements. By Fleming's Left hand rule on element $\\mathrm{AB}$ the direction of force will be Leftwards and the magnitude will be\n$$\n\\mathrm{dF}=\\operatorname{Idl} \\mathrm{B} \\sin 90^{\\circ}=\\mathrm{IdIB}\n$$<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/bitsat/XBTY49ILQHjW94fWn2TJCWNCt3sba5dlj7-xHNKczf4.original.fullsize.png\">", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGBSPYQ44963930", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "cpy